# Cursor Rules — Adaptek Web Portal

For all frontend code in this project:

## Stack
- Next.js 14 App Router with TypeScript (strict mode)
- Tailwind CSS utility classes — no inline styles
- React Server Components by default; add "use client" only when needed
- Static export for Firebase Hosting (`output: "export"` in next.config.ts)

## Code Quality
- No `any` types. No `ts-ignore` without explanation.
- Prefer `type` over `interface` for component props.
- Use `@/` alias for all imports (never `../`).
- Keep components under 150 lines. Split when larger.
- Use `cn()` from `@/lib/cn` for conditional class merging.

## Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA — Required, Not Optional)
- Semantic HTML: header, nav, main, section, footer
- Every section has `aria-labelledby` pointing to its heading
- Every image has descriptive `alt` text (or `alt=""` if decorative)
- All interactive elements are keyboard accessible with visible focus rings
- Form inputs always have associated `<label>` elements
- Error messages use `role="alert"` or `aria-live="polite"`
- Skip link in Navbar: `<a href="#main-content">Skip to content</a>`

## Brand Colors (use these, never raw hex)
- Primary: `brand-orange` (#FF7F2E), hover: `brand-orange-dark`
- Accent: `brand-green` (#3D9970)
- Text: `brand-charcoal` (#3A4A52)
- Background: `brand-offwhite` (#F9F8F6)

## Images & Fonts
- Always use `next/image` (<Image />) — never raw <img> tags
- Always use `next/font` for Google Fonts — never <link> in HTML

## Content Rules
- No lorem ipsum — use real Adaptek copy or mark with [TODO: copy]
- CTA primary: "Book a 30-minute consult"
- CTA secondary: "Download AI readiness checklist"
- Tone: professional, clear, human-centered, jargon-free

## Component Patterns
- Page sections: export default function XxxSection()
- UI primitives in src/components/ui/ — always include a *.test.tsx
- Assembly only in app/page.tsx — no logic there

## Do Not
- Do not use deprecated React patterns or class components
- Do not add heavy libraries for things Tailwind handles
- Do not commit .env files, .firebase/ folder, or firebase-debug.log
- Do not use outline:none without a replacement focus style
- Do not use raw hex colors — always reference brand tokens

## Reference
See CLAUDE.md for the complete rules, folder structure, and examples.
